title: Azhar Ali suffers infected foot, to miss first England Test
text: Azhar Ali suffers infected foot, to miss first England Test Sunday, 11 October 2015 (3 minutes ago) Azhar Ali, 30, suffered a foot infection during the Haj in Saudi Arabia last month. Pakistan suffered a blow before the first Test against England when team officials ruled out key batsman Azhar Ali. News24 1 hour ago - Sports Pakistan suffered a blow before the first test against England when team officials on Sunday ruled out key batsman Azhar Ali because of an infected foot. SuperSport 2 hours ago - Sports Pakistan's key middle-order batsman Azhar Ali is doubtful for the first Test against England starting in Abu Dhabi on Tuesday because of an infected foot. CricBuzz 3 hours ago - Sports Pakistan's key middle-order batsman Azhar Ali has been ruled out for the first Test against England starting in Abu Dhabi on Tuesday because of an infected foot.
